quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
  7,145,"And We wrote for him on the tablets [something] of all things - instruction and explanation for all things, [saying], ",footnotes:1:[This is a severe warning from Allāh against rebellion.]
  7,146,"I will turn away from My signs those who are arrogant upon the earth without right; and if they should see every sign, they will not believe in it. And if they see the way of consciousness,{1} they will not adopt it as a way; but if they see the way of error, they will adopt it as a way. That is because they have denied Our signs and they were heedless of them.",footnotes:1:[i.e., reason and integrity.]
  7,147,"Those who denied Our signs and the meeting of the Hereafter - their deeds have become worthless. Are they recompensed except for what they used to do?"
  9,49,"And among them is he who says, ",footnotes:1:[By avoiding their obligation, they fell into destruction.]
  9,50,"If good befalls you, it distresses them; but if disaster strikes you, they say, ",footnotes:1:[The hypocrites claim to have protected themselves by remaining behind.]
  9,51,"Say, "
  10,7,"Indeed, those who do not expect the meeting with Us and are satisfied with the life of this world and feel secure therein and those who are heedless of Our signs -"
  10,8,"For those their refuge will be the Fire because of what they used to earn."
  10,9,"Indeed, those who have believed and done righteous deeds - their Lord will guide them because of their faith. Beneath them rivers will flow in the Gardens of Pleasure."